1st-century%20versions%20of%20the%20brand.%20It%20was%20all%20the%20rage%2C%20known%20for%20low-rise%20jeans%2C%20shirtless%20men%2C%20and%20dimly%20lit%20stores%20that%20all%20but%20the%20most%20confident%20(or%20just%20obnoxious)%20customers%20would%20feel%20awkward%20walking%20into.%20It%20had%20its%20fair%20share%20of%20controversies%2C%20including%20allegations%20of%20racism%20and%20discrimination.%20Eventually%2C%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20once%20hot%20brands%2C%20be%20it%20Urban%20Outfitters%20or%20Von%20Dutch%2C%20it%20fell%20out%20of%20favor.%20(If%20you're%20a%20Gen%20Zer%20and%20do%20not%20know%20about%20The%20Thing%20that%20was%20Abercrombie%2C%20bless%20you%2C%20and%20also%2C%20there's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.netflix.com%2Ftitle%2F81323741%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix%20documentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20help.)%20When%20its%20longtime%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabercrombie-ceo-is-out-2014-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexited%20the%20company%20at%20the%20end%20of%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20sales%20had%20declined%20for%2011%20consecutive%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retail%20veteran%20Fran%20Horowitz%20was%20named%20CEO%20in%202017%2C%20and%20under%20new%20leadership%2C%20Abercrombie%20has%20turned%20things%20around.%20The%20company%2C%20which%20also%20owns%20the%20Hollister%20brand%2C%20reported%20net%20sales%20of%20%241%20billion%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20a%2022%25%20jump%20from%20the%20year%20before%2C%20and%20it%20expects%20net%20sales%20growth%20of%20about%2010%25%20for%20the%20year.%20In%20turn%2C%20investors%20have%20fallen%20for%20Abercrombie.%20A%20year%20ago%2C%20the%20stock%20was%20trading%20at%20about%20%2432.%20Now%20it's%20above%20%24180.%20Abercrombie's%20shares%20are%20up%20nearly%20100%25%20this%20year%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20big%20momentum%20play%20at%20this%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zachary%20Warring%2C%20an%20equity%20research%20analyst%20at%20CFRA%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Horowitz%20has%20pointed%20out%20on%20earnings%20calls%2C%20there's%20no%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20bullet%26quot%3B%20for%20Abercrombie's%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20been%20plugging%20along%20executing%20a%20playbook%20it%20set%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20Abercrombie%202.0%2C%20or%20whatever%20you'd%20like%20to%20call%20it%2C%20is%20more%20inclusive%20and%20welcoming.%20It's%20not%20for%20the%20scariest%20teens%20in%20your%20high%20school%20anymore%20but%20instead%20for%20adults%20in%20their%2020s%20and%2030s%20who%20want%20to%20look%20good%20and%20feel%20good%20and%20not%20have%20to%20think%20too%20hard%20about%20it.%20Abercrombie%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20trendy%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20fashion%20analyst%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F91010945%2Fhow-abercrombie-went-from-americas-most-hated-retailer-to-a-gen-z-favorite%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Fast%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20it%20wants%20to%20do%20classic%20silhouettes%20in%20classic%20colors%2C%C2%A0though%20it%20tosses%20in%20some%20prints%20and%20ruffles%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20carefully%20mapped%20out%20what%20it%20thinks%20its%20customers%20want%20when%20they're%20at%20the%20gym%2C%20at%20work%2C%20at%20happy%20hour%2C%20at%20a%20bachelorette%20party%2C%20on%20vacation%2C%20or%20wherever%20they'd%20be%20during%20a%20long%20weekend.%20It%20recently%20launched%20a%20weddings%20section%2C%20which%20has%20selections%20for%20guests%20and%20brides%2C%20for%20honeymoons%20and%20rehearsal%20dinners%20and%20receptions.%20Abercrombie%20has%20found%20success%20particularly%20with%20young%20women%2C%20though%20it's%20on%20the%20up%20and%20up%20with%20men%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20living%20their%20best%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Horowitz%20told%20Women's%20Wear%20Daily%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20better%20than%20being%20a%20young%20millennial.%20They%20live%20for%20the%20long%20weekend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKloppenburg%20said%20Abercrombie's%20success%20had%20come%20not%20just%20from%20changing%20up%20the%20look%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0clothes%20for%20all%20occasions%2C%20at%20a%20good%20price%20point%20%E2%80%94%20but%20from%20the%20company's%20execution%2C%20which%20has%20included%20focusing%20on%20smaller%20stores%20and%20running%20a%20lean%20inventory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20astute%20with%20inventory%20planning%2C%20with%20store%20payroll%20%E2%80%94%20and%20wages%20are%20up%20everywhere%20%E2%80%94%20with%20digital%20investments%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20wasn't%20just%20that%20the%20product%20was%20good%20in%20and%20of%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20since%20any%20rebrand%20is%20only%20as%20good%20as%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20know%20about%20it%2C%20Abercrombie%20has%20embraced%20social-media%20platforms%20such%20as%20TikTok%20and%20influencer%20marketing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20sell%20a%20lot%20of%20their%20products%20through%20affiliates%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20they%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20their%20marketing%20now%2C%20which%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20you%20pay%20attention%20to%20that%2C%20but%20in%20terms%20of%20apparel%20and%20retail%20companies%2C%20they're%20probably%20the%20best%20at%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Warring%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20really%20benefited%20from%20influencers%20taking%20their%20products%2C%20trying%20it%20on%2C%20and%20obviously%20posting%20the%20link%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAli%20Grant%2C%20a%20partner%20and%20the%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20at%20the%20Digital%20Dept.%2C%20an%20influencer-management%20company%2C%20told%20me%20that%20compared%20with%20other%20brands%2C%20Abercrombie%20tended%20to%20be%20less%20demanding%20about%20specific%20scripts%20for%20creators%20and%20to%20work%20with%20creators%20beyond%20%26quot%3Bfashion%20girlies%26quot%3B%20to%20reach%20a%20broader%20set%20of%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20really%20allow%20for%20creative%20exploration%20and%20direction%20from%20the%20content%20creator%20they've%20hired%2C%20which%20is%20really%20rare%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20made%20it%20more%20loose%20and%20more%20authentic%20and%20real%2C%20for%20lack%20of%20better%20words.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20opposed%20to%20the%20Abercrombie%20of%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20whose%20logos%20screamed%20A%26amp%3BF%2C%20the%20modern%20Abercrombie%20is%20muted.%20An%20influencer%20may%20be%20shilling%20for%20Abercrombie%2C%20but%20it%20feels%20much%20more%20item-forward%20than%20brand-forward.%20The%20point%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20was%20the%20name%3B%20now%20it's%20much%20more%20the%20clothes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20guarantee%20Abercrombie%20will%20be%20on%20top%20forever.%20American%20Eagle%20and%20Gap%20are%20starting%20to%20pull%20pages%20from%20the%20same%20playbook.%20(It's%20worth%20noting%20that%20not%20everything%20Abercrombie%20is%20doing%20is%20entirely%20original%2C%20and%20some%20of%20its%20pants%20look%20a%20lot%20like%20Aritzia's.)%20It%20looks%20as%20if%20Gap%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20brands%20Banana%20Republic%20and%20Old%20Navy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fretail-consumer%2Fgap-surges-apparel-makers-turnaround-strategy-starts-pay-off-2024-05-31%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20starting%20to%20turn%20itself%20around%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20get%20cool%20again%2C%20too.%20Kloppenburg%20pointed%20out%20that%20Abercrombie's%20operating%20margins%20were%20quite%20high%2C%20and%20if%20they%20decline%20or%20if%20the%20company%20starts%20having%20to%20discount%20more%2C%20that%20could%20spook%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20selling%20a%20lot%20of%20products%20at%20full%20price%20and%20full%20margin.%20And%20they%20make%20a%20few%20mistakes%2C%20and%20those%20margins%20start%20coming%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20when%20that%20happens%2C%20the%20stock%20will%20collapse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Abercrombie%20has%20pulled%20off%20something%20unique.%20Its%20customers%20are%20loving%20it%2C%20and%20so%20are%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20sound%20fundamental%20story%20as%20well%20right%20now%2C%20and%20it'll%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20over%20the%20next%2012%20to%2018%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20Warring%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20maybe%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20some%20flashy%20tech%20company%20to%20get%20Wall%20Street%20excited%2C%20nor%20do%20you%20have%20to%20be%20some%20elusive%20brand%20that%20makes%20people%20feel%20excluded%20to%20be%20successful.%20It's%20neat%20to%20see%20this%20kind%20of%20success%20story%2C%20where%20smart%20work%20and%20strong%20execution%20just%20%E2%80%A6%20pays%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabercrombie-and-fitch-stock-turnaround-millennials-weddings-wall-street-sales-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718186222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6667227ced9a404d829c219a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabercrombie-and-fitch-stock-turnaround-millennials-weddings-wall-street-sales-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Abercrombie%20%26amp%3B%20Fitch%20has%20turned%20itself%20around%20to%20become%20the%20darling%20of%20millennial%20women%20and%20Wall%20Street.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabercrombie-and-fitch-stock-turnaround-millennials-weddings-wall-street-sales-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20the%20typical%20LGBTQ%2B%20American%3A%20A%20homeowner%20making%20six%20figures%20who%20most%20likely%20lives%20in%20DC%20or%20Vermont%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22young%20lesbian%20couple%20laughing%20together%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66632f8fd0b8e1c832cd1c47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMore%20Americans%20are%20identifying%20as%20part%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community.%3Cp%3EMireya%20Acierto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EData%20offers%20a%20glimpse%20at%20the%20ages%2C%20races%2C%20and%20financial%20statuses%20of%20LGBTQ%2B%20Americans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDC%2C%20Vermont%2C%20and%20Massachusetts%20have%20the%20highest%20concentrations%20of%20same-sex%20couple%20households.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHistorically%2C%20limited%20LGBTQ%2B%20data%20collection%20has%20made%20it%20hard%20to%20identify%20the%20community's%20demographics.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20pride%20month%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20data%20shows%20that%20gay%20people%20exist%20year-round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20key%20data%20sources%20from%20the%20Census%20Bureau%20offer%20a%20snapshot%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20in%20America.%20Beginning%20in%20July%202021%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2021%2F08%2Fhousehold-pulse-survey-updates-sex-question-now-asks-sexual-orientation-and-gender-identity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHousehold%20Pulse%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20gauges%20the%20economic%20well-being%20of%20Americans%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20started%20collecting%20information%20on%20sexual%20orientation%20and%20gender%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Bureau's%20annual%20American%20Community%20Survey%20collects%20income%2C%20age%2C%20race%2C%20housing%2C%20and%20other%20demographic%20data%20for%20married%20and%20unmarried%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20although%20it%20has%20not%20collected%20data%20directly%20on%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20same-sex%20couples%20living%20in%20different%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20collection%20on%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Flgbtq-data-availability-what-we-can-learn-from-four-major-surveys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20historically%20limited%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fminorityhealth.hhs.gov%2Fimproving-data-collection-lgbt-community%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elead%20to%20further%20marginalization%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Flgbtq-data-availability-what-we-can-learn-from-four-major-surveys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Brookings%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20up%20to%2017.3%20million%20adults%20are%20not%20identified%20as%20LGBTQ%2B%20in%20the%20American%20Community%20Survey%20due%20to%20incomplete%20questions%20surrounding%20their%20sexual%20orientation%20and%20gender%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20American%20Community%20Survey%20(ACS)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsex-gender-lgbtq-census-american-community-survey-6409ef10f401b5e5526784f67ed5cfca%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20pilot%3C%2Fa%3E%20asking%20about%20sexual%20orientation%20and%20gender%20identity%2C%20potentially%20resulting%20in%20a%20trove%20of%20high-quality%20data%20on%20who%20in%20America%20is%20gay.%20But%20with%20the%20available%20data%2C%20here's%20what%20we%20know%20about%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cba3b099-7089-4d19-bd2e-8462ad12cf79%5C%22%3EDC%2C%20Vermont%2C%20and%20Massachusetts%20have%20the%20highest%20concentrations%20of%20gay%20couples%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20of%20individual-level%20Household%20Pulse%20Survey%20data%20from%20April%202024%2C%20around%203%25%20of%20the%20population%20identifies%20as%20gay%20or%20lesbian.%20A%20greater%20share%20%E2%80%94%20about%205%25%20%E2%80%94%20identifies%20as%20bisexual.%20And%20around%200.4%25%20of%20Americans%20identify%20as%20transgender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%201.7%25%20of%20those%20who%20identify%20as%20gay%20or%20lesbian%20also%20identify%20as%20transgender.%20Around%20a%20third%20of%20gay%20and%20lesbian%20adults%20are%20married%2C%20per%20HPS%2C%20compared%20to%20around%2058%25%20of%20straight%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EACS%20data%20from%202022%20shows%20that%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20has%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20same-sex%20couple%20households%2C%20at%203.6%25.%20Vermont%20has%20the%20next%20highest%2C%20at%201.8%25%2C%20followed%20by%20Massachusetts%20at%201.5%25.%20California%20has%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20same-sex%20households%2C%20at%20over%20162%2C100%2C%20followed%20by%20Texas%20at%20over%20107%2C200.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FcW887%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Percent%20of%20same-sex%20couples%20in%20each%20state%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20age%20of%20the%20householder%20of%20a%20married%20same-sex%20couple%20is%2048.6%2C%20compared%20to%2052.9%20for%20married%20opposite-sex%20couples.%20Among%20opposite%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20about%20a%20third%20are%20between%2025%20and%2044%2C%20while%20it's%2042%25%20for%20married%20same-sex%20couples.%20The%20age%20distributions%20were%20mostly%20similar%20for%20unmarried%20opposite-%20and%20same-sex%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FVVP7H%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Age%20of%20householder%20for%20same-sex%20couples%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22583%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ESame-sex%20couples%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20interracial%20than%20opposite-sex%20couples%20%E2%80%94%2032.2%25%20of%20same-sex%20couples%20are%20interracial%2C%20compared%20to%2018.6%25%20of%20married%20opposite-sex%20couples%20and%2028.6%25%20of%20unmarried%20opposite-sex%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESame-sex%20couples%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20bachelor's%20degrees.%20Overall%2C%2054.8%25%20of%20same-sex%20householders%20have%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%2C%20while%20both%20partners%20have%20degrees%2035.7%25%20of%20the%20time.%20For%20married%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20these%20values%20jump%20to%2057.3%25%20and%2038.2%25%20respectively.%20Meanwhile%2C%20these%20values%20are%2044.5%25%20and%2028.6%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20for%20married%20opposite-sex%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201b0788d-fbc6-4cdd-878a-d6e79fbe7502%5C%22%3EGay%20Americans%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20rent%20and%20earn%20more%20than%20straight%20families%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ACS%20data%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20same-sex%20couples%20make%20six%20figures%2C%20and%20the%20median%20household%20income%20for%20this%20demographic%20is%20%24110%2C600.%20For%20married%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20this%20number%20jumps%20to%20%24123%2C500%2C%20compared%20to%20%24109%2C700%20for%20married%20opposite-sex%20couples.%20Married%20male-male%20couples%20earn%20a%20median%20of%20%24138%2C700%20a%20year%2C%20while%20married%20female-female%20couples%20earn%20%24111%2C100%20a%20year.%20By%20contrast%2C%20unmarried%20same-sex%20couples%20make%20%2494%2C650%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eanalysis%20of%20individual-level%20data%20from%20the%20Household%20Pulse%20Survey%20shows%20the%20shares%20of%20gay%20and%20lesbian%20Americans%20in%20different%20income%20brackets.%20Around%209%25%20of%20gay%20and%20lesbian%20respondents%20report%20earning%20under%20%2425%2C000%20while%2010%25%20said%20they%20earned%20over%20%24200%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fpj5Am%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Incomes%20of%20gay%20and%20lesbian%20respondents%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22548%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2062.6%25%20of%20same-sex%20couples%20own%20their%20homes%2C%20while%2037.4%25%20rent.%20About%2072.7%25%20of%20married%20same-sex%20couples%20own%2C%20compared%20to%2081.9%25%20of%20married%20opposite-sex%20couples.%20Married%20male-male%20couples%20are%20slightly%20more%20likely%20to%20own%20homes%20than%20married%20female-female%20couples.%20Unmarried%20same-sex%20couples%20own%20just%2048.7%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20slightly%20above%2047.9%25%20of%20unmarried%20opposite-sex%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Household%20Pulse%20Survey%20data%2C%20around%2015%25%20of%20LGBTQ%2B%20Americans%20own%20homes%20outright%2C%20while%20around%2035%25%20own%20with%20a%20mortgage%20or%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FEf2Am%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Home%20tenure%20for%20opposite-%20and%20same-sex%20couples%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22332%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20same-sex%20couples%2C%20both%20partners%20are%20working%2C%20though%20this%20drops%20to%2061.9%25%20for%20married%20same-sex%20couples.%20However%2C%20same-sex%20couples%20are%20significantly%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20children%20in%20the%20household%20at%20just%2014.6%25%2C%20compared%20to%2038.1%25%20of%20married%20opposite-sex%20couples%20and%2034.5%25%20of%20unmarried%20opposite-sex%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20as%20more%20data%20emerges%20about%20who%20in%20the%20US%20is%20gay%2C%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20population%20is%20also%20getting%20bigger%20%E2%80%94%20underscoring%20the%20importance%20of%20capturing%20who%2C%20exactly%2C%20makes%20up%20this%20growing%20group.%20Recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F611864%2Flgbtq-identification.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20polling%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20around%207.6%25%20of%20American%20adults%20identify%20as%20non-heterosexual%2C%20up%20from%203.5%25%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20chalk%20some%20of%20that%20up%20to%20the%20youths%20%E2%80%94%20just%20over%2022%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20adults%20identify%20as%20LGBTQ%2B%2C%20suggesting%20that%20gay%20Americans%20could%20become%20an%20even%20bigger%20force%20in%20the%20not-so-distant%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpride-meet-typical-gay-lesbian-trans-queer-bisexual-lgbtq-american-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718186222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66632fba1cd3b17790447137%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpride-meet-typical-gay-lesbian-trans-queer-bisexual-lgbtq-american-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Around%203%25%20of%20Americans%20identify%20as%20gay%20or%20lesbian%2C%20and%205%25%20identify%