t%20refugees%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Matuas%2C%20who%20fled%20religious%20persecution%20in%20East%20Pakistan%20(now%20Bangladesh)%20and%20settled%20in%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA%20aims%20to%20facilitate%20citizenship%20for%20migrants%20belonging%20to%20Hindu%2C%20Sikh%2C%20Buddhist%2C%20Jain%2C%20Parsi%2C%20and%20Christian%20communities%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20who%20entered%20India%20on%20or%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%20The%20Matuas%2C%20who%20constitute%20over%2017%25%20of%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20are%20among%20those%20who%20stand%20to%20benefit%20from%20this%20amendment.%20They%20represent%20the%20second-largest%20SC%20group%20in%20the%20state%20after%20the%20Rajbongshis%2C%20who%20comprise%20more%20than%2018%25%20of%20North%20Bengal's%20SC%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20Await%20Recognition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20significant%20progress%20in%20granting%20citizenship%20to%20many%20Matuas%2C%20a%20large%20section%20still%20awaits%20recognition%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20proper%20documentation.%20Their%20concerns%20were%20further%20heightened%20by%20the%20prospect%20of%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20implementation%20in%20neighbouring%20Assam%2C%20where%20reports%20emerged%20of%20Hindus%20facing%20deportation%20due%20to%20inadequate%20identification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20citizenship%20rule%20amendments%20were%20welcomed%20in%20Matua-dominated%20areas%2C%20they%20faced%20opposition%20from%20the%20Rajbongshis.%20Organisations%20led%20by%20Rajbongshi%20leaders%20have%20been%20advocating%20for%20a%20separate%20state%20of%20Greater%20Cooch%20Behar%2C%20encompassing%20seven%20districts%20of%20North%20Bengal%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Kokrajhar%2C%20Bongaigaon%2C%20and%20Dhubri%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20June%209%2C%20when%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20cabinet%20took%20oath%2C%20a%20notable%20absentee%20was%20a%20young%20face%20from%20West%20Bengal.%20BJP's%20Nisith%20Pramanik%2C%20who%20won%20the%20Coochbehar%20Parliamentary%20seat%20with%20a%20significant%20margin%20in%202019%2C%20lost%20to%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20candidate%20in%20this%20election%20by%20over%2039%2C000%20votes.%20This%20defeat%20is%20viewed%20partly%20as%20a%20referendum%20reflecting%20the%20Rajbongshi%20organisations'%20perspective%20on%20the%20CAA%2C%20which%20they%20perceive%20as%20legitimising%20%26quot%3Billegal%26quot%3B%20residents%20in%20their%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERajbongshis%20Jittery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20BJP's%20efforts%20to%20reassure%20the%20Rajbongshis%20by%20nominating%20Ananta%20Rai%20(officially%20Nagendra%20Ray)%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20last%20year%2C%20tensions%20persisted.%20Rai%2C%20bearing%20the%20title%20of%20%26quot%3BMaharaj%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20descendant%20of%20the%20former%20ruler%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%2C%20distanced%20himself%20from%20Pramanik's%20election%20campaign%20even%20though%20Pramanik%20had%20reportedly%20played%20a%20role%20in%20Rai's%20nomination%20to%20the%20upper%20house%20of%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20constituencies%20in%20North%20Bengal%20with%20a%20significant%20Rajbongshi%20presence%2C%20such%20as%20Alipurduar%2C%20Jalpaiguri%2C%20and%20Darjeeling%2C%20the%20BJP%20secured%20victories%20with%20narrower%20margins%2C%20except%20in%20Raiganj%2C%20where%20its%20lead%20increased%20by%20approximately%208%2C000%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20seat%20dominated%20by%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Matua%20community%20in%20Bangaon%2C%20the%20BJP's%20Santanu%20Thakur%20retained%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%2C%20albeit%20with%20a%20reduced%20margin.%20In%20the%202019%20general%20election%2C%20he%20had%20defeated%20his%20aunt%20and%20TMC%20leader%20Mamat%20Thakur%2C%20the%20then-sitting%20MP%20from%20Bongaon%2C%20by%20over%201.1%20lakh%20votes%2C%20thus%20becoming%20the%20first%20non-TMC%20candidate%20to%20win%20in%20this%20constituency%20since%20its%20delimitation%20in%202009.%20Thakur%20also%20serves%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20All%20India%20Matua%20Mahasangha%2C%20headquartered%20in%20Bangaon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aunt%2C%20now%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%2C%20has%20been%20alleging%20that%20the%20CAA%20will%20do%20more%20harm%20than%20good%20to%20the%20refugees.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Santanu%20Thakur's%20margin%20of%20victory%20decreased%20to%20less%20than%2074%2C000%20votes%20in%202024.%20Interestingly%2C%20even%20the%20assembly%20segment%20of%20Bagdah%2C%20vacated%20by%20TMC%20candidate%20Biswajit%20Das%20to%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20against%20Santanu%20Thakur%2C%20gave%20the%20BJP%20candidate%20a%20lead%20of%20over%2020%2C000%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20For%20TMC%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20constituencies%20with%20a%20considerable%20presence%20of%20Matuas%2C%20such%20as%20Ranaghat%2C%20the%20BJP%20retained%20its%20seat%20with%20a%20slight%20decrease%20in%20margin.%20In%20adjoining%20Krishnanagar%2C%20the%20TMC%20retained%20the%20seat.%20Four%20of%20the%20assembly%20segments%2C%20mostly%20rural%20with%20a%20significant%20minority%20population%2C%20overwhelmingly%20supported%20the%20TMC%20candidate.%20The%20BJP%2C%20however%2C%20did%20well%20in%20urban%20Krishnanagar%20Uttar%2C%20leading%20by%20over%2053%2C000%20votes%2C%20and%20also%20in%20Krishnanagar%20Dakshin%20and%20Tehatta.%20Krishnanagar%20Uttar%20was%20won%20by%20former%20TMC%20leader%20Mukul%20Roy%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20polls%20on%20a%20BJP%20ticket%2C%20but%20he%20has%20been%20ailing%20and%20out%20of%20the%20public%20eye%20for%20some%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Tehatta%20favoured%20TMC%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20election%20when%20Tapas%20Kumar%20Saha%20beat%20the%20BJP's%20Ashutosh%20Paul%20by%20over%206%2C000%20votes.%20However%2C%20in%20the%202024%20parliamentary%20polls%2C%20the%20same%20segment%20gave%20the%20BJP%20candidate%20a%20lead%20of%20over%208%2C000%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElsewhere%2C%20in%20areas%20where%20the%20state%20witnessed%20protests%20after%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%202019%2C%20the%20TMC%20retained%20the%20Howrah%20and%20Murshidabad%20seats%20and%20captured%20Baharampur%20from%20five-time%20winner%C2%A0%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury.%20The%20minority-dominated%20areas%20saw%20the%20most%20protests%20as%20the%20bill%20excluded%20Muslim%20refugees%20from%20its%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20it%20is%20too%20early%20to%20dismiss%20the%20political%20implications%20of%20the%20CAA.%20The%20verdict%2C%20however%2C%20indicates%20that%20the%20CAA%20had%20a%20marginal%20impact%20on%20the%20outcome.%20It%20all%20boils%20down%20to%20how%20eligible%20applicants%20obtain%20citizenship%20in%20the%20future.%20Perhaps%20a%20clearer%20picture%20will%20emerge%20during%20the%20West%20Bengal%20assembly%20elections%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Jayanta%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%C2%A0writing%20on%20polls%20and%20politics%2C%20conflict%2C%20farmer%20and%20human%20interest%20issues)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718184660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-01%2Fui53k7m_mamata-banerjee-paints-to-protest-against-caa-pti_625x300_28_January_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-much-impact-did-caa-have-on-west-bengal-results-5873586%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20too%20early%20to%20dismiss%20the%20political%20implications%20of%20the%20CAA.%20The%20verdict%2C%20however%2C%20indicates%20that%20the%20CAA%20had%20a%20marginal%20impact%20on%20the%20outcome%20in%20West%20Bengal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-much-impact-did-caa-have-on-west-bengal-results-5873586%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Japan's%20prime%20Mount%20Fuji%20views%20are%20so%20prized%2C%20a%20Japanese%20developer%20is%20destroying%20a%20nearly%20complete%20apartment%20building%20to%20keep%20complaining%20neighbors%20happy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224242%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Picture%20of%20Mount%20Fuji%20from%20Fujikawaguchiko%20in%20Japan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662d343f23b29110d303e5ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222828%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPicture%20of%20Mount%20Fuji%20from%20Fujikawaguchiko%20in%20Japan.%3Cp%3EPHILIP%20FONG%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJapanese%20property%20developer%20Sekisui%20House%20is%20planning%20to%20demolish%20one%20of%20its%20newest%20developments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20decision%20came%20after%20neighbors%20complained%20that%20it%20blocked%20their%20view%20of%20Mount%20Fuji.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJapan's%20also%20erected%20mesh%20barriers%20to%20try%20to%20deter%20tourists%20from%20flocking%20to%20Mount%20Fuji%20hot%20spots.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Japan%20erected%20an%20eight-foot%20mesh%20barrier%20in%20front%20of%20a%20popular%20spot%20in%20the%20resort%20town%20of%20Fujikawaguchiko%2C%20where%20tourists%20flock%20to%20take%20pictures%20of%20Mount%20Fuji.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20it%20announced%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.channelnewsasia.com%2Feast-asia%2Fjapan-mount-fuji-dream-bridge-metal-fence-overtourism-photos-social-media-4391496%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etall%2C%20anti-tourist%20metal%20fence%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20another%20popular%20photo%20spot%2C%20the%20Mount%20Fuji%20Dream%20Bridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20quest%20to%20preserve%20these%20pristine%20views%2C%20however%2C%20just%20got%20more%20intense%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Japanese%20property%20developer%20has%20decided%20to%20knock%20down%20its%20nearly-finished%2010-storied%20condominium%20after%20neighbors%20complained%20that%20it%20would%20block%20their%20view%20of%20the%20snowy%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Grand%20Maison%20Kunitachi%20Fujimi%20Dori%20condominium%2C%20built%20by%20developer%20Sekisui%20House%2C%20is%20located%20in%20western%20Tokyo%2C%20in%20an%20area%20famous%20for%20its%20views%20of%20the%20country's%20highest%20mountain.%20The%20building%20is%20located%20on%20Fujimi%20Street%2C%20a%20picturesque%20viewing%20street.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sekisuihouse.co.jp%2Fcompany%2Ftopics%2Flibrary%2F2024%2F20240611%2F20240611r.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20developer%20said%20that%20it%20tried%20to%20change%20the%20condominium's%20design%20to%20reduce%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20view%2C%20but%20eventually%20decided%20to%20knock%20it%20down%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20concluded%20that%20the%20current%20situation%20has%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20landscape%2C%20and%20have%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20despair%20from%20Fujimi%20Street%20is%20a%20priority%2C%20and%20have%20independently%20decided%20to%20cancel%20this%20project%2C%26quot%3B%20Sekisui%20House%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20condominium%20comprised%2018%20housing%20units%2C%20priced%20from%20around%20%24445%2C000%20to%20%24646%2C000%2C%20per%20the%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-06-12%2Ftokyo-apartment-block-to-be-demolished-for-obscuring-mt-fuji-view%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20tenants%20were%20due%20to%20move%20into%20the%20condominium%20in%20a%20month's%20time%2C%20per%20Bloomberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20devel