ere-are-workers-moving-sarasota-tampa-florida-texas-linkedin-south-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJacksonville%2C%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-zoomtowns-housing-home-price-traffic-culture-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-orlando-florida-cheaper-homes-from-miami-california-ny-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrlando%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20each%20grown%20by%20more%20than%2020%25.%20On%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20most%20of%20the%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-exodus-population-drops-again-political-muscle-at-risk-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemigrating%20from%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20middle-class%20or%20lower-income%3B%20Texas%2C%20Arizona%2C%20and%20Florida%20are%20the%20states%20that%20have%20received%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-texas-moving-arizona-florida-expensive-housing-costs-washington-nevada-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elargest%20influxes%20of%20ex-Californians%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%202023%20analysis%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-of-living-nyc-millionaires-wealth-tax-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20state%20continued%20gaining%20millionaires%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20as%20overall%20population%20growth%20stagnated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20movement%20between%20cities%20and%20regions%20is%20good.%20Relocating%20to%20a%20new%20city%20can%20be%20a%20great%20way%20to%20raise%20your%20income%2C%20broaden%20your%20cultural%20horizons%2C%20or%20discover%20a%20sense%20of%20community%20and%20belonging.%20But%20America's%20current%20seismic%20reshuffling%20is%20something%20much%20less%20benign%20than%20a%20series%20of%20freely%20chosen%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20middle%20class%20flees%20superstar%20cities%2C%20those%20who%20are%20able%20to%20stick%20around%20are%20likely%20either%20too%20rich%20to%20care%20about%20housing%20costs%20or%20too%20poor%20to%20take%20on%20the%20expense%20of%20relocating%20somewhere%20more%20affordable.%20For%20one%2C%20this%20has%20dramatically%20reshaped%20regional%20job%20markets.%20The%20COVID-era%20transition%20to%20more%20remote%20work%20accelerated%20this%20process%20of%20%26quot%3Bdomestic%20offshoring%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adpri.org%2Flong-distance-work-and-domestic-offshoring%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20workforce-analytics%20company%20ADP%20found.%20Because%20there's%20less%20of%20a%20need%20for%20proximity%20between%20a%20firm's%20leadership%20and%20its%20employees%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-with-the-most-ceos-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexecutives%20have%20become%20more%20concentrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20high-cost%20metropolitan%20areas%2C%20while%20middle-class%20jobs%20have%20shipped%20off%20to%20areas%20with%20lower%20labor%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20areas%20that%2C%20not%20coincidentally%2C%20also%20tend%20to%20have%20lower%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20short%20run%2C%20middle-class%20job%20growth%20benefits%20regional%20economies%20in%20places%20like%20Austin%2C%20Raleigh%2C%20and%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20But%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20the%20high%20concentration%20of%20high-powered%20individuals%20in%20a%20select%20few%20metros%20is%20a%20disaster%20for%20social%20mobility.%20Domestic%20offshoring%20regionally%20segregates%20middle-%20and%20working-class%20employees%20from%20their%20employers%2C%20making%20it%20far%20more%20difficult%20for%20the%20former%20group%20to%20advance%20professionally.%20This%20not%20only%20creates%20a%20dangerous%20power%20imbalance%20between%20cities%20but%20hollows%20out%20formerly%20diverse%2C%20vibrant%20cultural%20scenes%20in%20some%20of%20America's%20biggest%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20America%20has%20sorted%20into%20high-cost%20regions%20and%20relatively%20affordable%20regions%2C%20class%20itself%20has%20become%20an%20increasingly%20regional%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20promise%20of%20mobility%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegional%20mobility%20and%20social%20mobility%20have%20long%20gone%20hand%20in%20hand.%20It%20wasn't%20just%20that%20the%20higher-wage%20starting%20positions%20tended%20to%20cluster%20in%20boomtowns%3B%20it%20was%20that%20residing%20in%20a%20boomtown%20put%20one%20in%20closer%20contact%20with%20all%20kinds%20of%20other%20opportunities.%20These%20might%20include%20the%20chance%20to%20network%20with%20executives%20or%20other%20employees%20further%20up%20the%20career%20ladder%3B%20exposure%20to%20more-remunerative%20adjacent%20professions%3B%20or%20access%20to%20investment%20capital%2C%20for%20those%20who%20want%20to%20start%20their%20own%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20relatively%20green%20developer%20from%20Nashville%20could%20move%20to%20the%20Bay%20Area%20and%20be%20able%20to%20rub%20shoulders%20with%20venture%20capitalists%20%E2%80%94%20and%20eventually%20entice%20those%20venture%20capitalists%20to%20provide%20the%20seed%20money%20for%20a%20new%20startup.%20The%20developer%20could%20even%20move%20their%20business%20back%20to%20Nashville%2C%20leveraging%20the%20connections%20from%20their%20time%20in%20California%20to%20bring%20new%20jobs%20to%20Tennessee.%20This%20dynamic%20cultural%20and%20economic%20exchange%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20possible%20if%20the%20developer%20had%20been%20unable%20to%20make%20the%20cross-country%20move.%20The%20opportunity%20loss%20would%20be%20even%20greater%20for%20a%20customer-service%20representative%20who%20wants%20to%20move%20into%20a%20higher-wage%2C%20higher-status%20role%20as%20a%20developer%20but%20doesn't%20have%20access%20to%20a%20professional%20network%20of%20developers%20because%20their%20employer%20keeps%20all%20those%20workers%20in%20a%20different%20metropolitan%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20the%20individual%20worker%20who%20loses%20out.%20When%20people%20get%20locked%20out%20of%20opportunities%20to%20raise%20their%20incomes%20or%20start%20new%20businesses%2C%20the%20national%20economy%20suffers.%20An%20influential%202019%20paper%20by%20the%20economists%20Chang-Tai%20Hsieh%20and%20Enrico%20Moretti%20found%20that%20low%20housing%20supply%20in%20superstar%20cities%20had%20significantly%20constrained%20US%20economic%20growth%20by%20limiting%20%26quot%3Bthe%20number%20of%20US%20workers%20who%20have%20access%20to%20the%20most%20productive%20of%20American%20cities.%26quot%3B%20Domestic%20offshoring%20threatens%20to%20lock%20in%20these%20effects%2C%20potentially%20costing%20the%20country%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20forgone%20wealth%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20superstar%20cities%20that%20ostensibly%20gain%20more%20influence%20also%20suffer.%20A%20city%20for%20managers%20and%20executives%20will%20never%20be%20a%20city%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20managers%20and%20executives%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20how%20many%20bosses%20relocate%20to%20New%20York%20City%2C%20they%20will%20always%20be%20a%20minority%20of%20the%20population.%20But%20if%20domestic%20offshoring%20persists%2C%20fewer%20of%20the%20city's%20other%20residents%20will%20be%20middle-class%20professionals%3B%20those%20people%20will%20tend%20to%20congregate%20in%20domestic-offshoring%20sites.%20Instead%2C%20the%20superstar%20cities%20will%20become%20luxury-service%20economies.%20Corporate%20leaders%20will%20still%20create%20jobs%20in%20places%20like%20San%20Francisco%20and%20New%20York%2C%20but%20they%20will%20be%20jobs%20for%20the%20support%20staffers%20who%20sustain%20the%20executive%20lifestyle%3A%20food%20servers%2C%20house%20cleaners%2C%20nannies%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20These%20cities%2C%20which%20are%20already%20deeply%20segregated%20and%20unequal%2C%20will%20become%20even%20more%20bifurcated%20between%20an%20elite%20class%20and%20a%20servant%20class.%20Beneath%20the%20servant%20class%2C%20and%20overlapping%20with%20its%20lower%20tiers%2C%20will%20be%20the%20large%20and%20growing%20ranks%20of%20the%20truly%20destitute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20this%20class%20system%20will%20suffer%20the%20most.%20But%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20this%20process%20will%20make%20us%20all%20poorer%2C%20costing%20us%20both%20forgone%20economic%20growth%20and%20the%20cultural%20vitality%20that%20can%20only%20be%20found%20in%20diverse%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMore%20beds%20for%20more%20heads%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20surefire%20way%20to%20reverse%20domestic%20offshoring%3A%20build%20more%20housing.%20Companies%2C%20the%20ADP%20study%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bhave%20an%20incentive%20to%20locate%26quot%3B%20individual%20and%20front-line%20workers%20%26quot%3Bin%20places%20that%20are%20more%20affordable%26quot%3B%20and%20where%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20translates%20into%20less%20upward%20pressure%20on%20wages.%20If%20housing%20in%20major%20cities%20were%20more%20affordable%2C%20that%20incentive%20would%20diminish%2C%20encouraging%20firms%20to%20spread%20the%20distribution%20of%20roles%20equally.%20Workers%20could%20move%20from%20one%20office%20to%20another%20in%20order%20to%20advance%20their%20careers%20or%20offer%20more%20value%20without%20worrying%20about%20the%20exorbitant%20cost%20of%20their%20new%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20pressures%20that%20lead%20to%20domestic%20offshoring%20are%20a%20lose-lose%20for%20all%20the%20cities%20involved%2C%20then%20changing%20course%20can%20be%20a%20win-win.%20Even%20as%20high-cost%20cities%20build%20more%20housing%20and%20work%20to%20reconstruct%20their%20middle%20classes%2C%20the%20growing%20Sun%20Belt%20cities%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20domestic%20offshoring%20can%20continue%20to%20thrive.%20They%20can%20do%20this%20by%20fostering%20diversified%20local%20economies%20%E2%80%94%20with%20their%20own%20local%20executive%20class%20%E2%80%94%20that%20are%20not%20reliant%20on%20any%20single%20large%20employer%20or%20industry.%20Further%2C%20they%20can%20avoid%20the%20mistakes%20of%20the%20larger%20cities%20and%20preemptively%20build%20plenty%20of%20dense%2C%20multifamily%2C%20infill%20housing.%20This%20will%20ease%20the%20upward%20pressure%20that%20a%20growing%20population%20puts%20on%20housing%20costs.%20It%20will%20also%20facilitate%20future%20population%20growth%2C%20which%20can%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20support%20a%20virtuous%20cycle%20of%20rising%20productivity%2C%20greater%20economic%20diversification%2C%20and%20further%20population%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20should%20not%20be%20to%20pick%20winners%20and%20losers%20among%20cities%20but%20to%20ensure%20economic%20integration%20%3Cem%3Ewithin%3C%2Fem%3E%20cities.%20Without%20such%20integration%2C%20the%20superstar%20cities%20face%20social%20and%20political%20collapse%2C%20while%20workers%20in%20domestically%20offshored%20jobs%20face%20narrower%20horizons%20for%20economic%20mobility.%20Society%20will%20end%20up%20sharing%20in%20the%20cost%3A%20If%20we%20allow%20our%20cities%20to%20become%20divided%20into%20imperial%20metropoles%20and%20economic%20hinterlands%2C%20we%20will%20all%20end%20up%20poorer.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20economic%20integration%2C%20and%20the%20productivity%20gains%20that%20come%20along%20with%20it%2C%20can%20make%20us%20all%20more%20prosperous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fned-resnikoff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENed%20Resnikoff%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20policy%20director%20of%20California%20YIMBY%20and%20co-leader%20of%20the%20Metropolitan%20Abundance%20Project.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-power-map-cities-ceo-executives-middle-class-jobs-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718184422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6668b3e1764df1611258bbe7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-power-map-cities-ceo-executives-middle-class-jobs-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Executives%20in%20New%20York%2C%20call%20centers%20in%20Orlando%3A%20American%20cities%20are%20facing%20a%20growing%20power%20imbalance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ned%20Resnikoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-power-map-cities-ceo-executives-middle-class-jobs-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20vs%20USA%20T20%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%3A%20How%20to%20watch%20live%20match%20free%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718184152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110936540%2Cimgsize-1353856.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-tips%2Findia-vs-usa-t20-cricket-world-cup-match-how-to-watch-the-live-match-free%2Farticleshow%2F110936540.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20is%20set%20to%20face%20the%20USA%20in%20a%20significant%20Group%20A%20match%20at%20the%20ICC%20Men%E2%80%99s%20T20%20World%20Cup%20at%20Nassau%20County%20International%20Cricket%20Stadium%20on%20Long%20Island%2C%20New%20York.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20Costco%20forklift%20driver.%20My%20job%20is%20essential%20to%20the%20warehouse's%20success.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20forklift%20driver%20unloads%20a%20truck%20at%20the%20Costco%20Distribution%20Center%20in%20Monroe%20Township%2C%20New%20Jersey%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6668bcdaed9a404d829cacff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMuch%20of%20Costco's%20operations%20revolve%20around%20forklifts.%3Cp%3EJames%20Leynse%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EForklift%20drivers%20are%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20warehouse%20operations%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounding-history-of-costco%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECostco%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20a%20challenging%20and%20sometimes%20stressful%20job%2C%20but%20one%20that%20earns%20a%20%242%20hourly%20wage%20premium.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Costco%20forklift%20driver%20in%20Chicago%20shares%20what%20the%20job%20is%20like.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20Chicago-area%20Costco%20forklift%20driver%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20as%20they%20are%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20with%20the%20media.%20Business%20Insider%20verified%20their%20identity%20and%20employment%20details.%20The%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Costco%20in%202011%2C%20starting%20out%20in%20the%20food%20court%2C%20and%20have%20done%20pretty%20much%20everything%20from%20merchandising%20to%20produce%2C%20deli%2C%20meat%20department%2C%20tire%20shop%2C%20and%20marketing.%20I%20was%20a%20supervisor%20in%20the%20warehouse%20and%20then%20ultimately%20settled%20down%20as%20a%20forklift%20driver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20Costco%20forklift%20drivers%20are%20seen%20kind%20of%20like%20supervisors%2C%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-treasure-hunt-layout-not-just-merchandise-tactic-superfans-say-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyou%20designate%20the%20flow%20of%20the%20building%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20either%20set%20it%20up%20for%20success%20or%20failure%2C%20depending%20on%20what%20goes%20on%20in%20the%20receiving%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20make%20more%20as%20a%20forklift%20driver%20now%20than%20I%20did%20ten%20years%20ago%20as%20a%20supervisor.%20My%20current%20wage%20is%20just%2020%20cents%20less%20than%20a%20supervisor's%20right%20now%2C%20so%20they%20hold%20you%20up%20to%20very%20similar%20standards.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnd%20it's%20fun%20driving%20a%20machine!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227d469b81-f6cc-4a0d-9e88-fa0c456d86e4%5C%22%3EWe%20help%20Costco%20sell%20huge%20amounts%20of%20stuff%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20today%20we%20were%20out%20of%20stock%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-ceo-signs-off-every-new-kirkland-signature-item-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKirkland%20Signature%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20a%20truck%20driver%20came%20in%20early%20with%2020%20pallets%20of%20it.%20And%20I%20know%20we're%20gonna%20sell%20that%20water%20as%20soon%20as%20we%20throw%20it%20out%20there%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20so%20I%20told%20him%20to%20back%20up%20to%20the%20dock%20door%2C%20and%20I%20unloaded%20it%20right%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20six%20hours%20early%2C%20plus%20we%20would%20have%20been%20closed%20at%20the%20time%20we%20were%20scheduled%20to%20unload%20him%2C%20so%20that's%2020%20pallets%20of%20water%20that's%20gonna%20sell%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20a%20different%20truck%20came%20that%20had%2024-packs%20of%20Monster.%20As%20soon%20as%20you%20unload%20them%2C%20they%20sell%20out%2C%20so%20that's%20another%20three%20pallets%20of%20sales%20for%20today%20that%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20added%20if%20I%20hadn't%20unloaded%20that%20truck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20look%20at%20the%20inventory%20on%20hand%20and%20work%20with%20the%20merchants%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20remove%20certain%20things%20from%20the%20floor%20and%20set%20the%20flow%20of%20the%20building%20because%20if%20we%20keep%20stuff%20in%20the%20truck%20and%20keep%20it%20back%20there%20on%20the%20dock%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20sell%2C%20and%20that's%20bad%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-costco-uses-large-packaging-for-tiny-products-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWe%20receive%20full%20truckloads%20of%20everything%20we%20need%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sorted%20by%20corporate%20and%20shipped%20out%20to%20us.%20The%20buyers%20look%20at%20our%20sales%20and%20see%20what%20we're%20projected%20to%20sell%20and%20they%20tell%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20depot%20to%20send%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20pallets%20to%20a%20given%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20a%20truck%20has%20a%20minimum%20of%2020%20pallets%20and%20a%20maximum%20of%2060%20pallets%20of%20items%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20heavy%20the%20items%20are.%20You%20don't%20really%20see%20smaller%20stores%20going%20through%20three%20truckloads%20of%20water%20or%20a%20truckload%20of%20paper%20towels%20in%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20truckload%20of%2060%20pallets%20of%20paper%20towels%2C%20each%20pallet%20has%2030%20sell%20units%2C%20so%20that's%201%2C800%20packs%20of%20towels.%20The%20sheer%20volume%20of%20things%20that%20go%20through%20our%20building%20is%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22309dc3a6-2fe6-4c86-9717-d2112aa96f22%5C%22%3ECostco%20takes%20safety%20incredibly%20seriously%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20actually%20a%20Costco%20forklift%20trainer%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECostco%20worked%20with%20OSHA%20to%20set%20up%20its%20own%20certification%20course.%20We%20have%20a%20third-party%20company%20that%20certifies%20all%20the%20trainers%2C%20but%20the%20trainers%20are%20all%20Costco%20employees.%20Every%20building%20has%20to%20have%20at%20least%20one%20trainer%20and%20they%20are%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20can%20train%20and%20certify%20Costco%20employees%20to%20operate%20the%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrainers%20are%20usually%20the%20more%20veteran%20drivers%20who%20have%20shown%20they%20know%20how%20to%20operate%20safely%20because%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20driving%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20drive%20a%20forklift%2C%20you%20actually%20don't%20have%20to%20drive%20fast%3B%20you%20have%20to%20drive%20smart%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20drive%20carefully%20because%20these%20forklifts%20weigh%20as%20much%20as%20three%20cars.%20The%20battery%20alone%20on%20a%20forklift%20weighs%20as%20much%20as%20a%20car%2C%20so%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20weight%20and%20power%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20only%20train%20one%20person%20at%20a%20time%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20we're%20giving%20them%20the%20attention%20they%20need%2C%20and%20then%20they%20get%20around%2020%20hours%20of%20supervised%20driving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20if%20we%20feel%20comfortable%20with%20how%20they%20drive%20and%20they've%20shown%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20safe%20drivers%2C%20we%20go%20through%20a%20checklist.%20They%20have%20to%20show%20proficiency%20in%20load%20placement%2C%20driving%20in%20the%20freezer%2C%20operating%20instructions%2C%20vehicle%20stability%2C%20and%20properly%20caring%20for%20the%20battery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20six%20months%2C%20we%20take%20them%20through%20an%20evaluation%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20still%20driving%20safely.%20If%20they've%20had%20no%20incidents%2C%20we%20give%20them%20full%20certification.%20Then%20they%20just%20have%20to%20recertify%20every%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20location%20hasn't%20had%20any%20notable%20accidents%2C%20but%20any%20major%20incidents%20in%20a%20warehouse%20are%20documented%20and%20shared%20with%20all%20the%20warehouses%20for%20review%20and%20to%20see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fforklift-worker-died-lumber-alabama-osha-dol-fine-sunbelt-forest-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20they%20could%20have%20been%20prevented%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20safety%20information%20being%20passed%20around%20throughout%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22776006bb-f4d0-4556-85e2-a9335b7a033e%5C%22%3EThere's%20always%20work%20for%20a%20forklift%20driver%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you're%20a%20forklift%20driver%2C%20there's%20zero%20turnover%20rate.%20We%20have%20a%20joke%20among%20Costco%20employees%20that%20forklift%20drivers%20think%20they're%20God's%20gift%20to%20the%20earth%20because%20they're%20always%20needed%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20pretty%20much%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20get%20offered%20overtime.%20Even%20when%20there's%20an%20overtime%20freeze%2C%20they'll%20still%20offer%20us%20overtime%20because%20they%20need%20us%20so%20badly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForklift%20drivers%20also%20get%20a%20%242%20premium%20on%20their%20hourly%20wage.%20Nobody%20ever%20wants%20to%20quit%20being%20a%20forklift%20driver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everybody%20can%20be%20a%20forklift%20driver%2C%20though.%20There%20can%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20stress%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20morning%20before%20the%20warehouse%20opens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20find%20somebody%20with%20the%20right%20mindset%20to%20be%20a%20forklift%20driver%20because%20it's%20not%20something%20that%20everybody%20can%20handle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20trainer%2C%20if%20I%20see%20you%20freaking%20out%20while%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostcos-hot-dog-combo-price-safe-cfo-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20a%20hot%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20want%20you%20driving%20a%205%2C000-pound%20machine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271ab337a-e071-4d09-9e3d-cd07a1090a7e%5C%22%3EEssential%20machines%20%E2%80%94%20and%20essential%20employees%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20there's%20a%20reason%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-costco-ceo-ron-vachris-life-career-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20new%20CEO%20used%20to%20be%20a%20forklift%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20always%20so%20much%20to%20do%2C%20and%20the%20work%20is%20never%20done.%20It's%20such%20an%20essential%20machine%2C%20specifically%20for%20Costco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20are%20you%20going%20to%20fit%202%2C000%20pallets%20of%20merchandise%3F%20You%20can't%20keep%20it%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20so%20you're%20gonna%20have%20to%20rack%20it%20on%20tall%20steel%20shelves%2C%20and%20you're%20gonna%20eventually%20have%20to%20bring%20that%20stuff%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20fit%20one%20pallet%20of%20chips%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-fun-facts-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20pallet%20of%20chips%20is%20gonna%20sell%20within%20an%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20you're%20gonna%20have%20to%20bring%20out%20a%20forklift%20and%20bring%20down%20another%20two%20pallets.%20Boom%2C%20let's%20go.%20Oh%2C%20and%20now%20you're%20out%20of%20Gatorade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20TVs%20are%20on%20sale%20for%20%24200.%20Guess%20what%3F%20You're%20gonna%20have%20to%20drop%20some%20more%20TVs%20down%20from%20the%20rack%20in%2020%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20we%20go%20out%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20we%20have%20a%20spotter%20in%20front%20and%20a%20spotter%20in%20back%2C%20and%20they%20kind%20of%20help%20keep%20people%20away.%20We%20also%20close%20the%20aisle%20that%20we're%20working%20on%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20aisle%20adjacent%20to%20us%20in%20case%20anything%20were%20to%20fall%20on%20the%20other%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20we%20have%20to%20work%20efficiently%20since%20those%20aisles%20aren't%20making%20sales%20if%20they're%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%242-an-hour%20incentive%20helped%20push%20people%20to%20want%20to%20be%20forklift%20drivers%20again.%20We%20want%20to%20work%20for%20Costco%2C%20but%20money%20talks.%20Offer%20us%20more%20money%2C%